# Canonical Repo Tree

## Purpose

This file is the human-maintained structure source of truth for the Hendren Platform repo.

Whenever modules are added, moved, split, consolidated, or removed, this file must be updated.

This file exists so that:

- the repo has one visible structural map,
- module placement stays intentional,
- folder drift is easier to catch,
- future cleanup and onboarding are faster,
- new modules have a canonical home.

## Rule

If the repo structure changes, this file changes in the same pass.

No exceptions.

## Status

Tree last updated: 2026-04-22. Reflects the current state of dev and the completed target tree for the current repo state after rewrite.

