## Completed Tree

### Purpose of this section

This is the completed target tree for the **current repo state after rewrite**.

It is not a future-scope wish list.
It assumes the current product scope remains the same and the repo is reorganized to match the approved module structure standard.

### Rewrite assumptions for the completed tree

- legacy root artifacts are removed from the active root,
- duplicate framework helper locations are consolidated,
- old working docs are retained but moved under archive,
- route files become thin,
- current large modules are decomposed into route-local private internals,
- shared UI is centralized into reusable inherited layers,
- current pricing worksheet UI becomes a shared pattern used by both price sheets and bids,
- current product scope is preserved rather than expanded.

