## Canonical Placement Rules

### Shared standards docs

All repo-structure governance docs belong in:

```text
docs/design/
```

### App routes

User-facing app routes belong in:

```text
src/app/
```

### Shared UI

Shared reusable UI belongs in:

```text
src/components/
```

### Shared domain logic

Authoritative business logic belongs in:

```text
src/lib/
```

### Supabase database changes

Schema and migration files belong in:

```text
supabase/migrations/
```

### Historical working docs

Legacy or historical working docs currently live under:

```text
docs/archive/
```

These should not be treated as the structural source of truth.
The structural source of truth lives in `docs/design/` plus the actual repo tree.

## Target Direction

As the rewrite proceeds, the tree should move toward the approved module structure standard defined in:

```text
docs/design/module_structure
```

That means future module areas should increasingly adopt:

- thin route files,
- route-local private internals,
- clearer shared UI inheritance,
- clearer shared domain ownership,
- fewer large god files.

## Maintenance Requirement

Whenever any of the following happens, update this file:

- new module added,
- module folder moved,
- route subtree reorganized,
- shared component area introduced or renamed,
- shared lib area introduced or renamed,
- major structural cleanup completed.

This file is not optional documentation.
It is part of the structure system.
